<br>
Raise Melee DPS back to 65% of a warrior<br>
Equally equiped bards (AA, attack, haste, items, weapons) do around 50% of warrior damage when they are attacking from behind and warriors are attacking from the front. This is below what bards should do.<br>
<br>
This problem hits hard especially on raids. After the first couple of any class, the remaining aspects players can add is DPS or healing. Since bards have such little DPS, after the first two, additional bards desirability in raids falls very low.<br>
<br>
The fact is, every other class can out DPS a bard (though it makes sense for some to perform their primary function such as healing). Why is a mostly melee hybrid the worst DPS class in EQ?<br>
As a hybrid, bards shouldn't be the worst at offense and defense. Every other melee/hybrid class excells in one of those categories.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Lower Fizzle Rates<br>
The minimum (max stats) missed notes is 6.1%. This translates to ~55 missed notes per hour (4 second cast time). At the very maximum, with max stats missed notes should be 5% (similar to other casters without specialization). Given that bards use 2 stats to (Cha/Dex) reduce missed notes, it should be reduced further.<br>
<br>
The missed note recovery AAs have too little effect. After spending 47 AAs, there is only a 20% recovery in missed notes, which translates to ~11 less missed notes per hour. The cost is too high for the returns. The returns (after 47AAs) should be 90-100% note recovery.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The Modifier Cap<br>
Bards with good instruments and all AAs can reach the modifier cap. This means that bards are not only limmitted by the instruments they can aquire, they can't reach thier maximum potential.<br>
With PoP instruments (4 expansions ago) and GoD AAs, bards hit the modifier cap. With GoD instruments, we surpass the mod cap, but are still bound, effectively making GoD instrument mods useless.<br>
No other class has to purchase AAs to increase their focus caps. Bards shouldn’t have to either.<br>
<br>
<br>
Better Mitigation<br>
Bards have the worst melee avoidance/mitigation even though bards are a plate class. This may be a result of our AC/avoidance softcap set too low or simply becuase our riposte, parry &amp; dodge base skills are too low. Many feel that silk casters can out survive bards when they are being attacked.<br>
Itemization (bard armor) has an AC that is also too low.<br>
<br>
<br>
Concerns for the new epic 1.5<br>
The second Dragon Necropolis fight in particular would appear more in line for the epic 2.0. This difficult raid and the one before it have no secondary drops, yet require raids of well-geared competent players to accomplish, making it difficult to convince those players to help. None of the items from the Dragon Necropolis raids are required for the final epic combine, yet we cannot complete our epic 1.5 without them. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jarethsun/ctvsig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
